import polars as pl
from plotnine import (
    ggplot,
    aes,
    after_stat,
    stage,
    geom_bar,
    geom_text,
    geom_label,
    position_dodge2,
    facet_wrap,
)
from plotnine.data import mtcars

chart = (
    ggplot(mtcars) +
    geom_bar(aes(x="factor(cyl)", fill="factor(cyl)"))
)

eggs =  pl.read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2023/2023-04-11/egg-production.csv')

(eggs
    .with_columns(
        year=pl.col('observed_month').str.to_date("%Y-%m-%d").dt.year(),
        )
    .group_by(["year","prod_type"])
    .count()
    .sort("year")
)

    + geom_bar()
    + geom_text(
        aes(label=after_stat("count")), stat="count", nudge_y=0.125, va="bottom"
    )
)

Code 
fast_food = (pl
    .read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2018/2018-09-04/fastfood_calories.csv", ignore_errors=True)
    .drop("") # 1st index column is unnamed and not required
)

chick_fil_a = (fast_food
    .filter(pl.col("restaurant")=="Chick Fil-A")
    .select(["item","total_fat","total_carb","protein"])
    .rename({'total_fat':'Fat', "total_carb":"Carbohydrates", "protein": "Protein"})
    .melt(id_vars="item", variable_name="Nutrients")
)
